^ The Oxford–AstraZeneca COVID-19 vaccine is codenamed AZD1222,[40] and later supplied under trade names, including Vaxzevria[41] and Covishield.[42]

^ Number of people who have received at least one dose of a COVID-19 vaccine (unless noted otherwise).

^ Percentage of population that has received at least one dose of a COVID-19 vaccine. May include vaccination of non-citizens, which can push totals beyond 100% of the local population.

^ Countries which do not report the number of people who have received at least one dose are not included in the world total.

^ Includes Freely Associated States

^ Includes Vatican City

^ This country's data are the number of vaccine doses administered, not the first dose only.
